column1: # Table S1. Genes Enriched or Depleted for Antisense 22G-RNAs in glp-4(bn2)
# Reads = number of reads antisense to and overlaping exon-exon juntions of the indicated gene
column2: normalized to the number of times each sequence perfectly matches the genome.
excluding reads considered to be degradation products

column1: # Ratio is calculated as: glp-4(bn2) / (glp-4(bn2) + wild-type) using the normalized read-norm value
# enriched / depleted - genes with a ratio <0.333 (2-fold or more depletion) are considered depleted. Genes with a ratio > 0.666 (2 fold or more enrichment) are considered enriched.
